description: <font color='#FF7F00'>Build a rocket</font> at the building area below, then use one of the <font color='#FF7F00'>launchers</font> to escape. <font color='#FF7F00'>Talk to Wisp Lee</font> when you land.

name: Journey to Ninjago!
description: Fly to Ninjago from Nexus Tower, then speak to Toshiro Gojira, the Battlefield Guard.

name: See the Sensei!
description: Use one of the side gates to get inside the Monastery. Then speak to Sensei Wu.

name: Unleash Spinjitzu!
description: Hold the attack button to charge your Spinjitzu - then release the button to unleash a Spinjitzu attack in front of Sensei Wu!

description: Smash Skeleton Troopers and Blacksmiths on the Ninjago Battlefield until you retrieve 5 Maelstrom Daggers.

description: Smash 5 Skeleton Ladders on the Ninjago Battlefield and rebuild them into Bouncers.

description: Find Bozu Roku, who is hiding in the first cave below the Monastery.

name: Trapped!
description: Rescue all 6 of the villagers in the Ninjago Caves.

name: Altars of Imagination
description: Smash 7 piles of debris in the Ninjago Caves and rebuild each one into an Altar of Imagination.

description: Smash 10 Skeleton Coffins on the Ninjago Battlefield before the Skeletons can pop out!

description: Find the Dragon Mask in a treasure chest hidden in the alcoves of the Cave of Black Echoes, below the Monastery.

name: Face of the Dragon
description: Equip the Dragon Mask so Zane can see how it looks.

name: Cole Fear
description: Equip the Dragon Mask and go to Cole in the Monastery Dojo of Earth. Then use the Speedchat menu to perform the Dragon Roar.

description: Find Cringe Lo, who is hiding somewhere in the Ninjago Monastery.

description: Go back to the Dojo of Lightning and tell Cringe Lo that Nya isn't interested in him.

description: Go to Bubu Mumu in the Ninjago Monastery and tell him that Cringe Lo has decided to quit his job.

name: Cringe Lo the Brave
description: Find Cringe Lo in the Ninjago Caves below the Monastery.

name: Alpha Dog
description: Smash Bone Wolves until you find 15 Tail Bones, then take them back to Furious Urufu in the Ninjago Monastery.

description: Find the 5 floating treasure chests that Johnny Thunder hid around the Ninjago Monastery.

description: <font color='#FF7F00'>Quick Build 1 button, 1 bouncer, and 1 moving platform</font> on the Monument.

name: Scarecrow
description: <font color='#FF7F00'>Scare 5 birds</font> off of the top of the Monument.

description: <font color='#FF7F00'>Talk to Wisp Lee</font> in Avant Gardens about a <font color='#FF7F00'>Maelstrom Cube</font> for Hu Where.

description: Smash 10 Skeleton Troopers and 3 Skeleton Commandos on the Ninjago Battlefield.

name: Fracture the Frontlines 2
description: Smash 8 Skeleton Blacksmiths and 3 Skeleton Marksmen on the Ninjago Battlefield.
